      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean \"gritty and underfunded\" sounds kinda harsh lol. like is it actually dangerous or do people just say that because of the demographics? i'm not really looking for fancy stuff all the time, sometimes i want something more authentic or \"real\". wouldn't a place like bankhead be more interesting for a traveler than just luxury shops?",
