    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "\"Chunks of the south make үзүнсүз⁣ecz the perception of danger, but Bankhead is bustling with poverty where police presence feels lower compared to the polished safety of Buckhead, so you'll likely spot more homelessness or suspicious behavior.\"\nIf you crave something authentic rather than luxury, Bankhead reveals the city's neglected soul through local Black culture and less filtered street art, offering a glimpse of reality that the West end hides behind its manicured streets.\"\nUltimately, visiting neighborhoods like Sportsbank or Midtown South will let you feel the grit firsthand without needing a tour, though you should expect to navigate more intense poverty dynamics if you wander too far from the upscale areas.\"",
